# Copy this file to `.env` for local development. `.env` is gitignored —
# never commit real values there, even though these two happen to be safe
# for a mobile client (see app.config.ts for why).
#
# EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL and EXPO_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY are read by
# app.config.ts and exposed to the app via Constants.expoConfig.extra
# (see src/lib/env.ts). The `anon`/`publishable` key is safe to embed in a
# shipped mobile client per standard Supabase practice — it identifies the
# project and is subject to RLS, not a secret credential. The service_role
# key must NEVER appear in this file, in app.config.ts, or anywhere in the
# mobile client.
